16 WHEREAS, her leadership and membership extends to The Links, Incorporated; Alpha
17 Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated; and the boards of the Boys and Girls Clubs of the
18 Chattahoochee Valley, Brookstone School, and Emanuel Preparatory School; and
19 WHEREAS, she is a graduate of Spelman College with a Bachelor of Arts in political
20 science and the University of Georgia with a Master of Education; and
21 WHEREAS, she has been widely recognized for her exemplary service, receiving an official
22 commendation from Senator Jon Ossoff for her advocacy on behalf of Georgia's families as
23 well as the Presidential Lifetime Achievement Award and special recognition from the
24 Biden-Harris Administration for her dedication to serving children and families; and
25 WHEREAS, Kornisha McGill Brown resides in Columbus, Georgia, with her husband, Dr.
26 Darius K. Brown Sr., and their children, Jordan Janay Brown and Darius Brown Jr.; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
28 extraordinary servant leader be appropriately recognized.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body congratulate and commend Kornisha McGill Brown for receiving
31 the 2025 Yellow Rose Nikki T. Randall Servant Leadership Award and extend best wishes
32 for her continued success.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
35 Kornisha McGill Brown.
